com.avaya.csta.physical

Class ButtonFunctionConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.avaya.csta.physical.ButtonFunctionConstants

  • public class ButtonFunctionConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    A type-safe enumeration for the buttonFunction parameter returned from PhysicalDeviceServices.getButtonInformation(). The button function (also called "button type") indicates what function a button performs, such as call forwarding or send all calls. The names used for the button function constants match the button names assigned to stations using the "add station" command on the System Administration Terminal (SAT). For example, a button called "call-appr" on the SAT corresponds to the button function constant called CALL_APPR. For a complete description of what each button does, consult your Avaya Communication Manager documentation.

    You might use the ButtonFunctionConstants defined in this class if you knew what button function you wanted to activate, but did not know which physical or soft button was administered to perform that function. In this case, you might follow these steps:

    1. Get the list of buttons administered for the device using the getButtonInformation method from PhysicalDeviceServices.
    2. Find the button in the buttonList that performs the desired function by comparing each button's function with the desired button function constant.
    3. Get that button's ID with buttonList.getButton().
    4. Create a ButtonPress object and set the button ID using ButtonPress.setButton().
    5. Invoke the pressButton method from PhysicalDeviceServices.

    Here is some sample code of how you might find and press the Call Forward button on a device: 

      // Create a ButtonPress request object and specify the device
  ButtonPress bpRequest = new ButtonPress();
  bpRequest.setDevice(device);

  // Create a GetButtonInformation object to enumerate all of the available
  // buttons
  GetButtonInformation biRequest = new GetButtonInformation();
  biRequest.setDevice(device);
  GetButtonInformationResponse biResponse = physDevServ.getButtonInformation(biRequest);
  ButtonList buttonList = biResponse.getButtonList();

  // Search the enumeration for the Call forward button
  for(Enumeration e = buttonList.enumerateButtonItem(); e.hasMoreElements();) {
      ButtonItem buttonItem = ((ButtonItem)e.nextElement());
      if (ButtonFunctionConstants.CALL_FWD.equals(buttonItem.getButtonFunction())) {
          // Specify the Call Forward button's ID in the ButtonPress request
          bpRequest.setButton(buttonItem.getButton());
      }
  }

  // Finally, press the Call Forward button
  physDevServ.pressButton(bpRequest);

    AVAYA, Inc.
